Comparison: Informed RRT* vs RRT* (no informed sampling)
Metric	Informed RRT*	RRT* (no informed)	Winner
Runtime	30 sec	30 sec	Same
Initial cost	44.74	51.38	Informed RRT*
Final cost	19.38	21.12	Informed RRT*
Iterations	12,507	19,533	RRT* (more iterations)
Cost improvement	44.74 → 19.38 (57% reduction)	51.38 → 21.12 (59% reduction)	Similar
Key Findings
Informed RRT* is clearly better:
9% better final cost (19.38 vs 21.12) in the same time
15% better initial solution (44.74 vs 51.38)
Fewer iterations but smarter sampling → each iteration is more valuable
Why RRT* (no informed) has more iterations but worse results:
Uniform sampling wastes effort in irrelevant regions
After finding a solution, it keeps sampling everywhere instead of focusing on the ellipsoidal region that could improve the path
More iterations ≠ better results when sampling is unfocused
